  "usageNotes": {
    "teacherGuidance": "Use a conversion chart on the board: 1 kg = 1000 g and 1 L = 1000 mL. Give children practice sheets with conversion problems. Start with whole numbers before mixed units.",
    "parentGuidance": "Practice conversions with food packets. Ask: This packet says 500 g. How many such packets make 1 kg? (Answer: 2 packets because 500 + 500 = 1000 g = 1 kg).",
    "studentGuidance": "Converting is like changing the unit. To go from kg to g, multiply by 1000 (add three zeros). To go from g to kg, think about how many groups of 1000 you have!"
  }
